# Appendix exercise A-3: class fields with prescribed split primes

This is Exercise III.3.15 of the source.  It defines `S`-class fields using ray
ideal groups and proves existence, uniqueness, and the Artin isomorphism

`I^(S union S(m)) / H ~= Gal(L/K)`.

The current development has local and finite-prime ideal infrastructure, but
does not yet package moduli, ray ideal groups, or the global class-field
existence theorem at the level required by this exercise.  Consequently no
weakened theorem is asserted here.
